(387, '2020-02-09 09:48:26', 'hchUkmkjDNc', 'MOOC', 0, 'e-Yantra MOOC: Overview of Crash Course on Embedded Systems and Robotics', 'e-Yantra has launched an exciting initiative exclusively for eLSI college students -an Online Certified Crash Course on Embedded Systems and Robotics.\nHere are few links for reference:\nPortal: http://mooc.e-yantra.org\nRegistration: http://mooc.e-yantra.org/auth/register\nSchedule: http://mooc.e-yantra.org/schedule\nFAQs: http://mooc.e-yantra.org/faq', '2020-05-20 11:39:19', '2020-06-08 11:03:25'),
(388, '2020-02-10 10:08:59', '3hJFxNzWP6s', 'MOOC', 0, 'IIT Bombay, e-Yantra: Online Certified Crash Course on Embedded Systems and Robotics (MOOC)', 'Prof. Kavi Arya, (PI, e-Yantra) recently spoke about the benefits of Crash Course on Embedded Systems and Robotics which is exclusively for eLSI colleges in e-Yantra family.\nHere are few links for reference:\nPortal: http://mooc.e-yantra.org\nRegistration: http://mooc.e-yantra.org/auth/register\nSchedule: http://mooc.e-yantra.org/schedule\nFAQs: http://mooc.e-yantra.org/faq', '2020-05-20 11:39:19', '2020-06-08 11:03:25'),
(389, '2020-02-27 03:08:12', 'aKeCph8bNIg', 'eYantra Impact', 0, 'e-Yantra Impact: Lt Gen AV Subramanian - Impact of e-Yantra', 'Gen. AV Subramanian, represents the \"Defence Innovation Space\", recently spoke about the impact of e-Yantra in all colleges. \n\nHe speaks about the foundation laid by e-Yantra for an innovation eco-system and how colleges can give full support to this and have e-Yantra lab in every college.\n\n#innovation #technology #ideas #eyic #eyantra #learnbydoing #startup #engineeringbettertomorrow #competition #industryconnect\n\nhttps://www.e-yantra.org/\nFacebook: https://www.facebook.com/eyantra/\nLinkedIn: https://www.linkedin.com/company/e-ya...\nInstagram: https://www.instagram.com/eyantra/\nTwitter: https://twitter.com/eyantra_iitb', '2020-05-20 11:39:19', '2020-06-08 11:03:25'),
(390, '2020-03-17 02:06:45', 'JWAEORu9FNE', 'eYantra Impact', 0, 'e-Yantra Impact: Journey of Suraj N from Drona Automation (e-Yantrik to Entrepreneur)', 'Suraj, is an entrepreneur working for a social cause where he has built a Sewer Cleaning Robot. His account here highlights the trials and tribulations of entrepreneurship. It\'s not an easy path but those who wish to make a difference are compelled to do what they do. For us Suraj is a role model for e-Yantriks. Be the change you wish to see. Solve a pressing problem that you see instead of leaving it for ”others.” We’ll bet that there are no real ”failures” in entrepreneurship. The entrepreneur will find a way out. \n\nSuraj’s  seed of entrepreneurship was sown during an e-Yantra Ideas Competition (eYIC). In the Regional Finals at Coimbatore, he highlights for us some important lessons - on how to convert our project into a product. Kudos to Suraj and other young people like him for making a real difference. 👏👏👏😊\n\n#eyic, #drona #automation, #e_yantrik, #studentproject, #entrepreneurship, #project #product, #sewagecleaningrobot, #innovation, #machinelearning #ml', '2020-05-20 11:39:18', '2020-06-08 11:03:25'),
(391, '2020-03-19 03:19:32', 'ovYpbinU2bI', 'eYIC', 2020, 'eYIC 2020: Impressions of e-Yantra Ideas Competition (eYIC) by Mr. C Kajwadkar', 'Mr. C Kajwadkar highlights the need for e-Yantra labs in every college and how students have worked on building original projects. Learning by doing will the students go onto become better engineers and in turn shape the future of our country.\n\n #eYantraIdeasCompetition, #eYIC, #studentproject, #entrepreneurship, #projecttoproduct, #ideas, #patents, #technical #paper #publication, #innovtion, #prototype #ownership', '2020-05-20 11:39:18', '2020-06-08 11:03:25'),
(392, '2020-03-19 03:23:55', 'LOLGapjJHYQ', 'eYIC', 2020, 'eYIC 2020: Impressions of e-Yantra Ideas Competition (eYIC) by Dr.  Anand Deshpande', 'Dr. Anand Deshpande  reinforces the need for practical learning in engineering colleges and how e-Yantra has played a crucial role in filling up that gap. He believes e-Yantra alumni have a bright future and is confident that some of them will become entrepreneurs in the near future.\n\n #eYantraIdeasCompetition, #eYIC, #studentproject, #entrepreneurship, #projecttoproduct, #ideas, #patents, #technical #paper #publication, #innovation, #prototype #teamwork, #confidence, #presentationskills, #patience, #perseverance, #leadership, #problemsolving, #positiveattitude, #timemanagement, #creativity, #criticalthinking, #personalitydevelopment, #handlefailure, #cooperation, #nevergiveup', '2020-05-20 11:39:18', '2020-06-08 11:03:25'),
(393, '2020-03-22 08:23:21', 'MwY99iM8VZg', 'eYIC', 2020, 'eYIC 2020: Impressions of e-Yantra Ideas Competition (eYIC) by Dr. Yogesh Kulkarni', 'Dr. Yogesh Kulkarni shares his opinion on the importance of the e-Yantra initiative that has changed the culture in engineering colleges across India.  It has transformed the way students learn engineering principles and concepts through  ”Learning by Doing.” \n\ne-Yantra is delighted to share this video and thanks Dr. Kulkarni for sharing his insights.\n\n #eYantraIdeasCompetition, #eYIC, #studentproject, #entrepreneurship, #projecttoproduct, #ideas, #patents, #technical #paper #publication, #innovation, #prototype #teamwork, #confidence, #presentationskills, #patience, #perseverance, #leadership, #problemsolving, #positiveattitude, #timemanagement, #creativity, #criticalthinking, #personalitydevelopment, #handlefailure, #cooperation, #nevergiveup #learnbydoing', '2020-05-20 11:39:18', '2020-06-08 11:03:25'),
(394, '2020-03-22 11:18:33', 'MW3OfzbG-DM', 'eYantra Impact', 0, 'e-Yantra Impact: Journey from e-Yantrik to an Entrepreneur - Muthu Vangaliappan', 'Muthu Vangaliappan is an e-Yantra alumnus of our first e-Yantra Robotics Competition (eYRC-2012).\n\nHere he showed us that entrepreneurs are great storytellers. He had us totally engaged and often in splits in this spontaneous record as he recounted his journey as a participant in the e-Yantra Robotics Competition (eYRC) to an entrepreneur. \nHis experience highlights the \"can do\" spirit and persistence that the competition brings out in students as they learn by confronting challenging problems and better themselves in developing innovative solutions to them.\n\ne-Yantra team wishes all the best to Muthu.. 🙌\n\n#learnbycompeting #eYantraRoboticsCompetition, #eyrc, #learn&compete, #nationalroboticscompetition, #training, #eyrc, #competition, #challenges, #teamwork, #teammanagement #teamwork, #confidence, #presentationskills, #patience, #perseverance, #leadership, #problemsolving, #positiveattitude, #timemanagement, #creativity, #criticalthinking, #personalitydevelopment, #handlefailure, #cooperation, #nevergiveup #SuccessStories #entrepreneur', '2020-05-20 11:39:18', '2020-06-08 11:03:25'),
