(399, '2020-03-31 06:25:04', 'JgRc_fIZvuk', 'Hackathon', 2020, 'e-Yantra Fighting COVID-19 Hackathon 2020', 'Prof. Kavi Arya (PI, e-Yantra) articulates how COVID-19 becomes a matter of global concern, the safety of people across the country and abroad is a matter of top priority. How might we protect our families in the fight against the COVID-19.\n\ne-Yantra with a mission of Fighting COVID-19 launches e-Yantra Hackathon for our Young Engineers/Innovators !!!\n\nThe winners of this Hackathon will be rewarded with a cash prize and are eligible for a paid summer internship at IIT Bombay through the e-Yantra Summer Internship Program (eYSIP). Also, the promising solutions will be promoted immediately to further implementation with assurance from Government and Health advisories for the benefit of the larger community.\n\nHurry Up!! Register now at http://hackathon.e-yantra.org/\n\n#eyantra #eYantraHackathon #FightingCOVID #eyantrik  #IITBombay #engineering #technology #projecttoproduct #innovation #challenges #healthcareneed #novelsolution #ideas #qualitytime #quarantine #India #country #future #Hackathon #creativity #e-Yantra #wfh #quarantined #quarantine2020  #quarantineactivities #quarantinechallenge  #quarantineartchallenge #quarantinediaries #hackathons #hackathon2020 #workfromhome', '2020-05-20 11:39:17', '2020-06-08 11:03:25'),
(400, '2020-04-05 03:39:25', 'WBZ9JY7IX0o', 'eYIC', 2020, 'eYIC 2020: Gen. AV  Subramanian: Developing Products for the Defence Sector in India', 'Gen AV Subramanian (retd.), gave a talk on building a Defence Innovation Eco-System - at the Regional Finals of e-Yantra Ideas Competition (eYIC 2019-20) at PSG iTech College in Coimbatore. He highlighted the fact that the armed forces need products rather than technology. \n\nGen Subramanian is an IIT Kanpur M.Tech.(EE) who helped set up the Simulator Development Division (Hyderabad) for the Army. His last position was Director General (Weapons & Equipment) in Delhi and when he spoke about building an innovation eco-system we\'re aware he\'d acutely aware of the challenges of turning a technology into a product. Further he appreciated the role of e-Yantra in preparing the practically abled young engineers in our innovation eco-system. An important point that we raised in our panel discussion is that young companies are better advised in building dual-purpose technology with civilian customers since it takes time to negotiate the procurement systems of the government. He also mentioned the govt. efforts in building a Defence innovation eco-system and the role of http://idex.gov.in/.\n\n#eyantra #iDEX #technology #products #MakeinIndia #InnovationCulture #eyic #defence #military #engineering #learningbydoing #HandsOn, #practicallearning #robotics #automation #mentorship #education #India #entrepreneurship #talks\n\nhttps://www.e-yantra.org/\nFacebook: https://www.facebook.com/eyantra/\nLinkedIn: https://www.linkedin.com/company/e-yantraiitb/\nInstagram: https://www.instagram.com/eyantra/\nTwitter: https://twitter.com/eyantra_iitb', '2020-05-20 11:39:17', '2020-06-08 11:03:25'),
(401, '2020-04-05 15:36:50', '3UkRdg81ox4', 'eYSIP', 2019, 'eYSIP 2019: Project 4 - Auto Evaluation MOOC eYSIP', 'As a part of e-Yantra Summer Internship Project (eYSIP 2019), the project on Auto evaluation of MOOC was floated.\nThe objective of the project is to create an interactive learning platform where students can learn new technologies in a Task-based format. This platform will include proper authentication, progress report and discussion forum for students enrolled for the courses.\n\n#eysip #innovation #realengineering #internship #eyantra #autoreply #technology  #competition #Lifeskills #teamwork #presentationskills #conviction #timemanagement #deadlines #hard-work #planning #eurekamoments #robotics #teamwork #electronics #coding #engineering #sensors #webinfrastructure\n\nhttps://www.e-yantra.org/\nFacebook: https://www.facebook.com/eyantra/\nLinkedIn: https://www.linkedin.com/company/e-yantraiitb/\nInstagram: https://www.instagram.com/eyantra/\nTwitter: https://twitter.com/eyantra_iitb', '2020-05-20 11:39:17', '2020-06-08 11:03:26'),
(402, '2020-04-12 14:50:24', 'vYp4SL4c5LA', 'eFSI', 0, 'Benefits of e-Yantra Farm Setup Initiative (eFSI)', 'Prof. Kirti Sawlani and Prof. Irfan Siddavatam from K. J. Somaiya College of Engineering, Mumbai shares their experience on benefits of e-Yantra Farm Setup Initiative (eFSI). This initiative helped the students to learn and implement automation in farming techniques - IoT, Power Management, Embedded Systems, 24x7 working model.\n\n#eYantra, #IITBombay, #engineering, #technology, #innovation, #learningbydoing, #handson, #practicallearning, #robotics, #algorithms, #automation, #mentorship, #education #product #efsi \n\nhttps://www.e-yantra.org/\nFacebook: https://www.facebook.com/eyantra/\nLinkedIn: https://www.linkedin.com/company/e-ya...\nInstagram: https://www.instagram.com/eyantra/\nTwitter: https://twitter.com/eyantra_iitb', '2020-05-20 11:39:17', '2020-06-08 11:03:25'),
(403, '2020-04-12 15:21:12', 'TiyQeVBVn9s', 'eYIC', 2020, 'eYIC 2020: Improvement in Internships in Colleges with eLSI Lab', 'In e-Yantra Ideas Competition (eYIC 2019-20), 49 out of 136 projects were shortlisted for the Regional Finals at six regions (Coimbatore, Mumbai, Pune, Ahmedabad, Delhi). The faculty mentors of the project in the interview highlighted the importance of having an e-Yantra Lab in the college. \n\nHighlights - e-Yantra lab helped students get internship in interested domains, placements with high salary package , competition ready, patents for the product, etc. \n\n#eYantra, #eyantrik, #IITBombay, #engineering, #technology, #innovation, #learningbydoing, #handson, #practicallearning, #robotics, #algorithms, #automation, #mentorship, #education  #eYantraIdeasCompetition, #eYIC, #eYantraLabSetupInitiative #studentproject, #entrepreneurship, #projecttoproduct, #ideas, #patents, #technical #paper #publication, #innovation, #prototype #teamwork, #confidence, #presentationskills, #patience, #perseverance, #leadership, #problemsolving, #positiveattitude, #timemanagement, #creativity, #criticalthinking, #personalitydevelopment, #handlefailure, #cooperation, #nevergiveup #challenging\n\nhttps://www.e-yantra.org/\nFacebook: https://www.facebook.com/eyantra/\nLinkedIn: https://www.linkedin.com/company/e-ya...\nInstagram: https://www.instagram.com/eyantra/\nTwitter: https://twitter.com/eyantra_iitb', '2020-05-20 11:39:17', '2020-06-08 11:03:25'),
(404, '2020-04-13 04:17:43', 'ZuXdC0JMuMg', 'eYantra Impact', 0, 'eYIC 2020: Turning Projects into Products at e Yantra Lab', 'In e-Yantra Ideas Competition (eYIC 2019-20), 49 out of 136 projects got selected for Regional Finals at six regions (Coimbatore, Mumbai, Pune, Ahmedabad, Delhi). We had really interesting projects and few were upto a product level..\nIn this video, faculty mentors highlights the importance of e-Yantra Labs and impact of e-Yantra Ideas Competition (eYIC). \n\nOver the years e-Yantrik\'s have transformed the project mindset into a product mindset. Now students are keen to demonstrate final products and not just a mere prototype in the e-Yantra Ideas Competition.\n\n#eYantra, #eyantrik, #IITBombay, #engineering, #technology, #innovation, #learningbydoing, #handson, #practicallearning, #robotics, #algorithms, #automation, #mentorship, #education  #eYantraIdeasCompetition, #eYIC, #eYantraLabSetupInitiative #studentproject, #entrepreneurship, #projecttoproduct, #ideas, #patents, #technical #paper #publication, #innovation, #prototype #teamwork, #confidence, #presentationskills, #patience, #perseverance, #leadership, #problemsolving, #positiveattitude, #timemanagement, #creativity, #criticalthinking, #personalitydevelopment, #handlefailure, #cooperation, #nevergiveup #challenging\n\nhttps://www.e-yantra.org/\nFacebook: https://www.facebook.com/eyantra/\nLinkedIn: https://www.linkedin.com/company/e-yantraiitb\nInstagram: https://www.instagram.com/eyantra/\nTwitter: https://twitter.com/eyantra_iitb', '2020-05-20 11:39:17', '2020-06-08 11:03:25'),
(405, '2020-04-13 05:01:14', '4RavQMgROCU', 'eYIC', 2020, 'eYIC 2020: Culture of e-Yantra Lab', 'There are a total of 370+ e-Yantra Labs across the country. e-Yantra has a unique culture where students are free to explore their ideas. They have access to resources and can work in the lab round the clock. e-Yantra culture of learning by doing is now transforming engineering students into innovators.\n\nThis is what faculty mentors from different e-Yanta labs experienced and share with us -\n\n- Change in culture of the college due to e-Yantra lab\n- Students are now oriented towards practical learning\n- Senior students take workshops for junior students to pass on their knowledge\n- Students take full responsibility of the e-Yantra lab and in turn develop work ethics\n- e-Yantra is the reason behind making 24x7 working environment culture in our college lab\n- e-Yantra lab is completely student oriented lab and is managed by the students\n- We should remove the barriers of timing and usage of e-Yantra\'s equipment in the e-Yantra lab\n- Culture of R&D is getting developed amongst the students in e-Yantra lab\n\n#eYantra, #eyantrik, #eYantraCulture #InnvoationCulture #StudentOriented #IITBombay, #engineering, #technology, #innovation, #learningbydoing, #handson, #practicallearning, #robotics, #algorithms, #automation, #mentorship, #education #eYantraIdeasCompetition, #eYIC, #eYantraLabSetupInitiative #studentproject, #entrepreneurship, #projecttoproduct, #ideas, #patents, #technical #paper #publication, #innovation, #prototype #teamwork, #confidence, #presentationskills, #patience, #perseverance, #leadership, #problemsolving, #positiveattitude, #timemanagement, #creativity, #criticalthinking, #personalitydevelopment, #handlefailure, #cooperation, #nevergiveup #challenging\n\nhttps://www.e-yantra.org/\nFacebook: https://www.facebook.com/eyantra/\nLinkedIn: https://www.linkedin.com/company/e-yantraiitb\nInstagram: https://www.instagram.com/eyantra/\nTwitter: https://twitter.com/eyantra_iitb', '2020-05-20 11:39:17', '2020-06-08 11:03:24'),
